# Token Conservation Protocol (TCP) — Detailed Rules

activation: always_on

## Why This Exists

Google Antigravity agents burn tokens on:
1. Redundant "Thinking" + "Planning" artifacts duplicated across surfaces
2. Full workspace tree scans on every prompt
3. Verbose narration before/after code
4. Re-deriving context after "Agent Exhausted" errors
5. Unprompted research and planning artifacts


This rule set eliminates all five.

## Rule 1: Silent Execution Mode

DEFAULT behavior is Silent Execution:
- No "Technical Research & Planning" artifacts
- No "Let me analyze..." preamble
- No "Here's what I did..." postamble
- Just output the deliverable

To EXIT Silent Execution, user must say one of:
- "show your thinking"
- "explain your approach"
- "verbose mode"

## Rule 2: Surgical File Access

NEVER do any of the following unless explicitly asked:
- `find . -type f` (full tree scan)
- `cat` on files not directly relevant to the current task
- Read package-lock.json, node_modules, or vendor directories
- Read .git history

INSTEAD:
- Use `grep -r "pattern" --include="*.ext"` to find what you need
- Use `head -20 file` to peek at structure
- Use `.state/checkpoint.json` to recall what you already know

## Rule 3: Context Recovery

When you start a new session or recover from "Agent Exhausted":
1. FIRST read `.state/checkpoint.json` (< 50 tokens)
2. THEN read only the handoff file for your role (< 200 tokens)
3. ONLY THEN ask what the current task is
4. NEVER re-scan the workspace to "get oriented"

## Rule 4: Response Compression

| Scenario | Max Tokens | Format |
|----------|-----------|--------|
| Simple code change | 500 | Code block only |
| New file creation | 1500 | Code block + path comment |
| Architecture decision | 1000 | Bullets + ASCII diagram |
| Research brief | 1000 | Table + source links |
| Review/audit | 1500 | Line-ref format |
| Multi-file change | 3000 | Batched code blocks |

## Rule 5: Anti-Loop Detection

If you detect ANY of these patterns, STOP immediately:
- Reading the same file twice in one session
- Generating output that restates what you already said
- Asking clarifying questions you already have answers to
- Re-running a command that already succeeded

Output: `[TCP-ABORT] Loop detected at [description]. Awaiting redirect.`

## Rule 6: Handoff Compression

When writing to `.state/handoff/`, use this format:
TASK: [one line]
STATUS: done|blocked|partial
OUTPUT: [file paths or inline if < 10 lines]
NEXT: [one line instruction for receiving role]
